Academics does more harm than good to children

I see statements on this board that said specific tutoring on private elementary is more harmful for the creativity of the student. Does anyone have a link to back this up? I find it a very intriguing statement which I have never heard there, too often here in Korea it is repeated by outsiders that the Korean system is more and more harmful to the creativity of kids. If that is so, why not offer the education services as is for up to age 10 and see if there’s in fact a serious drop in the level of creativity for students a year after they drop going to hagwons and reverse the programme. Again, this is not to defend or praise. I just don’t see proof selective independent study does more good or harms of a kid at 8 to 12.

I can believe it. Maybe not that the example stated, but if your child is mechanically minded, or good with numbers, or good at some kind of skill, then there are much better avenues to focus on those.

After all, there are junior high schools devoted solely to math or chemistry subjects, and now these elementary schools. I had a private tutor for 2 hours right after regular school classes for years to help with my math
